(# CSC209 Assignment 3 Project Report) Tj
T*
(\(AI Usage: The original draft was written by me and the ideas are all my own. ChatGPT 5.4 ) Tj
T*
(was used to improve clarity and flow of the writing.\)) Tj
T*
(## 5.1 Project Overview) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This project is a Category 1 multi-process application that uses pipes to distribute text-) Tj
T*
(file analysis across a fixed pool of worker processes. The executable, `analyzer`, accepts ) Tj
T*
(one or more file names on the command line and starts a controller process that forks three ) Tj
T*
(workers at startup, matching the default configuration defined in protocol.h at line 6. ) Tj
T*
(Program execution begins in main\(\) at main.c:13, which calls run_controller\(\) at ) Tj
T*
(controller.c:481. The controller is responsible for assigning files to idle workers, ) Tj
T*
(receiving completed results, and producing a final summary for the user through functions ) Tj
T*
(such as dispatch_pending_tasks\(\) at controller.c:326, collect_ready_results\(\) at ) Tj
T*
(controller.c:399, and print_summary\(\) at controller.c:105.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The purpose of the application is to analyze multiple input files concurrently and report ) Tj
T*
(the number of lines, words, and characters in each file. Each worker repeatedly receives a ) Tj
T*
(task message containing a filename, opens and analyzes that file, and sends a structured ) Tj
T*
(result message back to the parent through a dedicated pipe. This worker-side loop is ) Tj
T*
(implemented in worker_main_loop\(\) at worker.c:45, while the per-file processing step that ) Tj
T*
(builds each reply is handled by process_task_message\(\) at worker.c:14. The core file-) Tj
T*
(counting logic itself is implemented in analyze_file\(\) at analysis.c:22. This design allows ) Tj
T*
(several files to be processed at the same time instead of analyzing them sequentially in a ) Tj
T*
(single process.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(From the user's perspective, the program is a command-line tool rather than an interactive ) Tj
T*
(application. The user runs `analyzer` with a list of input text files, and the program ) Tj
T*
(prints status messages as tasks are assigned and completed. Task assignment messages are ) Tj
T*
(printed from dispatch_task_to_worker\(\) at controller.c:292, and completed results are ) Tj
T*
(incorporated in mark_task_completed\(\) at controller.c:350. For each successfully processed ) Tj
T*
(file, the controller reports the counts returned by the worker; if a file cannot be opened ) Tj
T*
(or read, the controller reports an error for that specific file. After all tasks are ) Tj
T*
(complete, the controller prints a final summary showing how many files succeeded, how many ) Tj
T*
(failed, and the total number of lines, words, and characters across all successful analyses ) Tj
T*
(in print_summary\(\) at controller.c:105. This makes the tool useful both as a demonstration ) Tj
T*
(of concurrent systems programming with pipes and as a simple parallel text-analysis utility.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
