T*
() Tj
T*
(Each worker has exactly one task pipe \(controller writes, worker reads\) and one result pipe ) Tj
T*
(\(worker writes, controller reads\). The controller waits on all live result pipes in ) Tj
T*
(collect_ready_results\(\) at controller.c:399, where poll\(\) is used so the parent is never ) Tj
T*
(blocked on a single worker. When the controller has no more tasks to dispatch it sends a ) Tj
T*
(MSG_SHUTDOWN TaskMessage in send_shutdown_to_workers\(\) at controller.c:136 and later reaps ) Tj
T*
(child processes through reap_worker_if_possible\(\) at controller.c:115.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 5.4 Communication Protocol) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This project uses a fixed-width binary protocol defined in protocol.h, with the TaskMessage ) Tj
T*
(struct beginning at protocol.h:20 and the ResultMessage struct beginning at protocol.h:30. ) Tj
T*
(Every message sent over a pipe is stored in one of these C structs and written with one call) Tj
T*
( to write_full\(\) at ipc.c:35, which repeatedly calls write until the entire struct has been ) Tj
T*
(transmitted or an error occurs. On the receiving side, read_full\(\) at ipc.c:7 repeatedly ) Tj
T*
(calls read until the exact number of bytes for the expected struct has been received, or ) Tj
T*
(until it detects end-of-file, a short read, or another error. As a result, the receiver ) Tj
T*
(always knows exactly how many bytes to read: workers always read sizeof\(TaskMessage\) from ) Tj
T*
(their task pipe in worker_main_loop\(\) at worker.c:45, and the controller always reads ) Tj
T*
(sizeof\(ResultMessage\) from a worker result pipe in collect_ready_results\(\) at ) Tj
T*
(controller.c:399.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The message types are identified by the type field in each struct. The valid values are ) Tj
T*
(MSG_TASK, MSG_SHUTDOWN, and MSG_RESULT, defined in the MessageType enum at protocol.h:10-13.) Tj
T*
( For parent-to-worker traffic, both normal work requests and shutdown notices use the same ) Tj
T*
(TaskMessage struct. For worker-to-parent traffic, completed analysis results use the ) Tj
T*
(ResultMessage struct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Message Type: MSG_TASK) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Sender and receiver: Controller to worker.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Encoding: A fixed-size TaskMessage struct written in binary form in a single write_full ) Tj
T*
(call. The struct contains an integer type field, an integer task_id field, and a fixed-size ) Tj
T*
(filename array.) Tj
ET
