T*
(termination depending on the case. If the worker receives a TaskMessage whose type field is ) Tj
T*
(not MSG_TASK or MSG_SHUTDOWN, it treats that as a protocol violation and exits.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Message Type: MSG_SHUTDOWN) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Sender and receiver: Controller to worker.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Encoding: A fixed-size TaskMessage struct written in binary form in a single write_full ) Tj
T*
(call. The controller sets type to MSG_SHUTDOWN and uses task_id = -1. The filename field is ) Tj
T*
(left empty.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(typedef struct {) Tj
T*
(       int32_t type;) Tj
T*
(       int32_t task_id;) Tj
T*
(       char filename[512];) Tj
T*
(} TaskMessage;) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Semantics and invariants: This is a control message rather than a work request. It tells a ) Tj
T*
(worker that no more files remain to be processed and that it should terminate normally. The ) Tj
T*
(controller sends this message in send_shutdown_to_workers\(\) at controller.c:136. The worker ) Tj
T*
(still reads exactly sizeof\(TaskMessage\) bytes before interpreting the message in ) Tj
T*
