(endpoints, re-queues any task that was still assigned to that worker, and calls waitpid with) Tj
T*
( WNOHANG through reap_worker_if_possible\(\) so that the dead child can be collected without ) Tj
T*
(blocking the rest of the program. During final cleanup, after the controller has sent ) Tj
T*
(MSG_SHUTDOWN to all remaining live workers in send_shutdown_to_workers\(\) at ) Tj
T*
(controller.c:136, cleanup_controller\(\) calls waitpid without WNOHANG through ) Tj
T*
(reap_worker_if_possible\(\) to reap any children that are still running. This prevents zombie ) Tj
T*
(processes and ensures that all child processes are collected before the program exits.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 5.6 Error Handling and Robustness) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This project checks the return values of all important system calls and treats pipe ) Tj
T*
(failures, malformed messages, and file-processing errors as normal runtime conditions that ) Tj
T*
(must be handled explicitly. The design goal, implemented across run_controller\(\) at ) Tj
T*
(controller.c:481, collect_ready_results\(\) at controller.c:399, and analyze_file\(\) at ) Tj
T*
(analysis.c:22, is that a single bad input file or a single worker failure should not ) Tj
T*
(immediately crash the entire program unless no workers remain able to make progress.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(One bad behaviour is that a worker may fail or disconnect while it is processing a task. ) Tj
T*
(This can happen if the worker exits unexpectedly, crashes, or closes its result pipe before ) Tj
T*
(sending a complete reply. The collect_ready_results\(\) function at controller.c:399 detects ) Tj
T*
(this through poll events such as POLLHUP or POLLERR, or through read_full\(\) at ipc.c:7 ) Tj
T*
(returning end-of-file, a short read, or a general read error. The controller then calls ) Tj
T*
(handle_worker_failure\(\) at controller.c:262, which marks the worker as dead, closes the ) Tj
T*
(worker's pipe file descriptors, re-queues any task that had been assigned to that worker, ) Tj
T*
(and attempts to reap the child with waitpid through reap_worker_if_possible\(\) at ) Tj
T*
(controller.c:115. This allows the remaining live workers to continue processing the ) Tj
T*
(unfinished work.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A second bad behaviour is that the controller may receive malformed or inconsistent data ) Tj
T*
(from a worker. For example, a result message might have the wrong type field, an invalid ) Tj
T*
(task identifier, or a task_id that does not match the task currently recorded as running for) Tj
T*
( that worker. The controller checks all of these conditions in collect_ready_results\(\) at ) Tj
T*
(controller.c:399 and mark_task_completed\(\) at controller.c:350 before accepting a result. If) Tj
T*
( any of these invariants fail, the controller treats the result as a protocol error rather ) Tj
T*
(than silently accepting corrupted state. It marks the worker as failed through ) Tj
T*
(handle_worker_failure\(\) at controller.c:262, closes the associated pipes, and re-queues the ) Tj
T*
(unfinished task if necessary. This prevents incorrect counts from being added to the final ) Tj
T*
(totals.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A third bad behaviour is failure while writing to a pipe. If the controller cannot send a ) Tj
T*
(TaskMessage to a worker because write_full\(\) at ipc.c:35 fails inside ) Tj
T*
(dispatch_task_to_worker\(\) at controller.c:292, it assumes that the worker is no longer ) Tj
T*
(usable and handles it as a worker failure. If a worker cannot send a ResultMessage back to ) Tj
T*
(the controller because the result pipe has been closed or another write error occurs, ) Tj
T*
(process_task_message\(\) at worker.c:14 prints an error with perror and exits with failure. ) Tj
T*
(The program also ignores SIGPIPE in main\(\) at main.c:13 so that a broken pipe does not ) Tj
T*
(terminate the process abruptly; instead, the failed write is reported through the normal ) Tj
T*
(error path and handled explicitly.) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
