() Tj
T*
(A fourth bad behaviour is that an input file may be invalid or unreadable. For example, the ) Tj
T*
(file may not exist, the process may not have permission to open it, or a read error may ) Tj
T*
(occur while scanning the file. In analyze_file\(\) at analysis.c:22, the code checks the ) Tj
T*
(return values of open, read, and close. If any of these operations fail, it stores the ) Tj
T*
(corresponding errno value and human-readable message in the AnalysisResult structure. The ) Tj
T*
(worker then places that information in a ResultMessage in process_task_message\(\) at ) Tj
T*
(worker.c:14 with success set to false, and the controller reports the file-specific error in) Tj
T*
( mark_task_completed\(\) at controller.c:350 without terminating the rest of the program. This) Tj
T*
( means one bad input file does not prevent other files from being analyzed successfully.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A fifth bad behaviour is an invalid filename that is too long to fit in the fixed-size ) Tj
T*
(protocol buffer. Before sending a task to a worker, dispatch_task_to_worker\(\) at ) Tj
T*
(controller.c:292 checks whether the filename fits inside the TaskMessage filename field. If ) Tj
T*
(it does not, the controller does not send a truncated or malformed message. Instead, ) Tj
T*
(fail_task_locally\(\) in controller.c at line 278 marks the task as failed, records an ) Tj
T*
(ENAMETOOLONG error, increments the failed-task count, and continues processing the remaining) Tj
T*
( files. This avoids corrupting the protocol while still giving the user a clear explanation ) Tj
T*
(of the failure.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The main limitation of the current implementation is that it does not spawn replacement ) Tj
T*
(workers after a crash. Instead, robustness comes from re-queuing unfinished work in ) Tj
T*
(handle_worker_failure\(\) at controller.c:262 and continuing with the surviving worker ) Tj
T*
(processes. If all workers die before all tasks have completed, ) Tj
T*
(report_all_workers_dead_if_needed\(\) in controller.c at line 471 detects that no further ) Tj
T*
(progress is possible, and run_controller\(\) at controller.c:481 exits cleanly rather than ) Tj
T*
(hanging indefinitely.) Tj
T*
() Tj
